# Testing Rules

Every business rule requires tests.

Tests must cover where applicable:
- happy path; invalid/missing input; duplicate trigger
- retry behavior; provider/API failure; forbidden side effect
- status transition; idempotency; recovery/escalation

Tests must map to Given/When/Then from:
- `/docs/security-observability-testing.md`
- `/docs/business-process-map.md`

DB integration tests: follow `.cursor/rules/docs-selection/70-testing.mdc` (`npm run test:integration`, Testcontainers).

Task is incomplete if:
- only compiles or only happy path is tested
- side effects can happen before validation
- lifecycle changes lack tests, undocumented behavior is added, or process mapping is bypassed

## Coding Rules

Use TypeScript strict mode.

Forbidden:
- unjustified `any`; magic strings for statuses/enums
- hardcoded secrets; undocumented env variables
- silent catch blocks; broad catch without handling/rethrow
- business logic in controllers/repositories/integrations
- speculative abstractions
- premature queues/CQRS/event sourcing/microservices/workflow engines unless documented

Preserve names from `/docs`.

## Required Task Note Before Coding

Before coding, output:

Task:
- what will be implemented

Docs read:
- paths from `.cursor/rules/docs-selection/` for this task (always include `/docs/decision-log.md`)

Business process step:
- mapped step from `/docs/business-process-map.md`

V1 scope:
- included
- excluded

Files planned:
- files to create/change

Validation:
- tests/checks to run

Open decisions:
- `TODO_DECISION` items, if any

Then implement only the scoped task.

## TODO_DECISION Format

Use when a required decision is missing:

TODO_DECISION:
- Decision needed:
- Context:
- Why it blocks safe implementation:
- Affected module/files:
- Suggested options:
- Recommended default, if safe:
- Owner: Architect/Product Owner

Do not continue the blocked area until resolved.

## Completion Checklist

Before claiming completion, verify:

- V1 only; matches `/docs`; no undocumented concepts; no V2/V3
- model layers separated; business logic not in controller/repository/integration
- statuses/lifecycle match docs; validation before side effects; idempotency respected
- failures handled; tests cover Given/When/Then; forbidden behavior tested
- no secrets leaked; no unjustified `any`
- no unresolved `TODO_DECISION` in completed scope

If any item fails, do not claim completion; report issue and required fix.
